footnotes: The Cambodia socio-economic survey includes information on household expenditures on health in two different modules: a household level module on non-food expenditures and a individual level module on health care seeking and expenditures. The observation value reported here comes from the latter. When using the former the proportion of the population with household expenditures on health larger than 25% of total household expenditure or income  is equal to 3.6%.
